                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh98002075 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579 http://lccn.loc.gov/n94096736" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4056-part1-item1">
                        <locus from="1v" to="32v">ff. 1v-32v</locus>
                        <note>
                           <p>Fragment of a mas̲navī in praise of the ruler of Avadh, <persName key="person_4638161696247516120008" role="subject">Vazīr al-mamālik Navvāb Āṣaf al-Dawlah</persName>, recounting his exploits and, especially, his expedition to and from <placeName>Rāmpūr (Uttar Pradesh State)</placeName> following <persName key="person_f7125" role="subject">Fayz̤ Allāh Khān</persName>’s killing of <persName key="person_f7337" role="subject">Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān</persName> in 1209
                           </p>
                           <p>Āṣaf al-Dawlah is occasionally referred to as Navvāb-i Jannat Ārāmgāh, indicating the poem may have been composed after his death
</p>
                           <p>William Irvine labels the work <title>Āṣafnāmah</title>, but this is not found in the present work
                           </p>
                           <p>Colophon (f. 32v): completed on the road to <placeName>ʿAẓīmābād (Patna, Bihar State)</placeName>, Thursday afternoon, 10 Shaʿbān 1221/23 October 1806
                           </p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
