                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89003718" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4056-part2-item1">
                        <locus from="33r" to="37v">ff. 33r-37v</locus>
                        <note>
                           <p>Collection of varied poems in qiṭʿah, mas̲navī, and tarkīb forms, including mars̲iyah, comprising selections from the work of named poets: 1) <persName key="person_19217849" role="aut">ʿAbd al-Jalīl Bilgrāmī</persName>; 2) <persName key="person_f7544" role="aut">Shāh ʿAbd Allāh</persName>; 3) <persName key="person_33415216" role="aut">Niʿmat Khān "ʿĀlī"</persName>
                           </p>
                           <p>Considered previously to be part of the mas̲navī (part 1), but this is not the case. Part 2 is transcribed by the same hand as the first, but the forms, genres, and subjects are different 
</p>
                           <p>Collection ends abruptly without colophon, though datable to the same period as part 1 
</p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     </msItem>
